Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "plavo" in different forms and positions with translations in English:

1. *Plavo* more je duboko i hladno. (The *blue* sea is deep and cold.)
2. Sviđa mi se tvoja *plava* majica. (I like your *blue* shirt.)
3. Kada sam bila mala, imala sam jednu igračku koja je bila *plave* boje. (When I was little, I had a toy that was *blue*.)
4. *Plavom* bojom sam obojila zidove u dnevnoj sobi. (I painted the walls in the living room with *blue* paint.)
5. Vidim da ti je pogled usmeren prema *plavom* nebu. (I see that your gaze is directed towards the *blue* sky.)
6. Danas sam se obukla u *plavo*. (Today I dressed in *blue*.)
7. *Plavi* patlidžan je moj omiljeni sastojak u kuvanju. (Eggplant is my favorite ingredient in cooking.)
8. Oči su mi *plave* boje kao more u letnjoj noći. (My eyes are *blue* like the sea on a summer night.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "plavo" can be used as an adjective (e.g. "plava majica" - "blue shirt"), a noun (e.g. "plavo more" - "blue sea"), or an adverb (e.g. "obukla se u plavo" - "dressed in blue"). Additionally, the word "plav" can be used as an adjective in its masculine form (e.g. "plavi patlidžan" - "blue eggplant"), while "plave" is its feminine form (e.g. "plave oči" - "blue eyes").